-- Indonesia’s Kharisma Sells 8,500 Tons of Palm Oil
-- B y   E k o   L i s t i y o r i n i
-- 2012-01-10T11:34:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/indonesia-s-kharisma-sells-8-500-tons-of-palm-oil-table-.html
PT Kharisma Pemasaran Bersama
Nusantara , which sells  palm oil  from  Indonesia ’s state-owned
plantations, sold 8,500 metric tons of the 14,000 tons of the
commodity it offered at an auction in Jakarta today.  Yesterday, the company sold 7,500 tons of palm oil in an
auction at prices ranging from 8,683 rupiah a kilogram ($947 a
ton) to 8,533 rupiah.  The following table lists the results of the sale, based on
a faxed statement. The volumes are given in metric tons, while
prices are in rupiah per kilogram including a 10 percent value
added tax, unless stated otherwise.  Indonesia is the world’s largest producer of palm oil.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eko Listiyorini in Jakarta at 
